        <h2>Communications and Network Expertise for Patent Litigation</h2>

        <p>A seasoned expert witness in patent litigation, Dr. Lavian brings experience in academic and industrial research and a Ph.D. from UC Berkeley specializing in telecommunications and network communications. With decades of expertise in the field, he has established himself as a trusted authority in complex technical matters within the communications and networking domain.</p>

        <p>His expertise extends to computer networks, data communications, LAN/WAN, TCP/IP, UDP, VPN, VoIP, streaming media, chat, SMS, mobile wireless, Ethernet, routing, switching, Internet, and web technologies. This comprehensive knowledge base allows him to provide authoritative analysis on a wide range of network and communications technologies and their applications in real-world systems.</p>

        <p>Dr. Lavian offers expert witness services in patent cases, including expert testimony, expert witness reports, and patent analysis of Internet technologies, standards, and protocols. He has testified in Federal courts before judges and juries, the USPTO PTAB, and the ITC, bringing credibility and depth to litigation matters involving complex technical subjects.</p>

        <p>With support on IP litigation cases related to over 140 patents in network communications and telecommunications, his experience spans cases involving leading companies such as Amazon, LinkedIn, Avaya, Netflix, T-Mobile, ZTE, Ericsson, Cisco Systems, Juniper Networks, Arista, Polycom, Motorola, LG, WhatsApp, Instagram, Microsoft, Google, Huawei, Facebook, Apple, and others.</p>

        <p>Having testified as an expert witness over 70 times in depositions and trials and having written numerous expert reports, Dr. Lavian combines academic rigor with practical litigation experience to deliver compelling expert witness services tailored to the needs of IP practitioners and their clients.</p>

